# Gemini Project Notes & Guidelines

This file contains useful findings, domain knowledge, and development instructions learned during our sessions.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Guidelines for Future Sessions**: Always record any new project-specific useful notes, domain knowledge, script workflows, or troubleshooting tips to this file at the end of each session so we continue to learn and build context as we go.

---

## 🎾 LTTA Domain Knowledge

### 1. League Structure
- **League Name**: La Crosse Team Tennis Association (LTTA).
- **Match Format**: Set scoring with 1 point per set won (including tiebreakers) and 1 point for participation (showing up on time).
- **Team Count**: 12 teams for both Tuesday and Wednesday nights.
- **Round-Robin**: Standard round-robin rotation takes 11 weeks (each team playing the other 11 once).
- **Start Times**: Matches rotate between 5:30pm and 7:00pm on Green Island Park courts.
- **PICNIC & CROSSOVER**: The season concludes with a picnic and crossover championship matches between Tuesday and Wednesday teams, plus winningest lines.

### 2. Tuesday Team 2 (`Subs`)
- Tuesday Team 2 is the **`Subs`** team (with roster players Sawyer Kuck, Dave Mills, etc.). 
- When rosters are regenerated, ensure it is named `Subs` rather than defaulting to `BYE`.

### 3. Logan Alternate Location (Retired)
- Previously, matches were moved to **`Logan`** courts when Green Island `Courts 1–5` were unavailable at `5:30pm` due to early-season conflicts.
- This override has been completely removed in May 2026. All matches now show they are at Green Island (using standard court groups like `Courts 1–5`).

---

## 🛠️ Management Scripts & Workflow

### 1. Roster Column Mapping
- The Google Sheet uses `Name` as the player name column header (older sheets used `1-Name`).
- All scripts (`create-roster.js`, `generate-rr.js`, `create-emails.js`) must support both `Name` and `1-Name` mapping to avoid empty rosters and default `"BYE"` names.

### 2. Typical Regeneration Workflow
Always run scripts in this order from the project directory (or within `management-scripts` folder adjusting paths):
1. `node management-scripts/create-roster.js` (creates JSON rosters)
2. `node management-scripts/generate-rr.js` (generates schedules and ICS calendars)
3. `node management-scripts/generate-all-html.js tuesday` and `node management-scripts/generate-all-html.js wednesday` (creates printable full-season schedules)
4. `node management-scripts/create-emails.js` (onboarding emails)
5. `cd management-scripts && node generate-scoresheet.js` (creates printable weekly scoresheet files)

